JOHANNESBURG - At least 13 people have died in two major crashes at the start of the holiday weekend. Four people were killed in a crash between two cars on the N4 toll road near Middelburg. READ:Â At least six people dead in KZN crash And nine people have died and at least 14 others have been injured in a horror crash on Ou Kaapse Weg in Steenberg, Cape Town. Just before 2 am paramedics arrived on the scene where they found a single vehicle, which had overturned several times. All of the dead were men. What caused the vehicle to roll is still not known at this stage and investigations are underway.